translated:
Lundberg, Sven Ivar, surgeon at Renströmska Hospital, Gothenburg, born on June 6, 1891 in Uppsala to practical physician Karl Ivar L. and Hulda Maria Dorotea Wallin. Married in 1920 to Anna Stina Berggren, who holds a Bachelor's degree in Philosophy. Children: Kerstin, born in 1922, Ulla in 1924, and Arendt in 1926, who is currently studying medicine. 

Education: Completed high school in Uppsala in 1909, obtained a Bachelor's degree in medicine there in 1912, a medical license in Stockholm in 1917, and a doctorate in medicine there in 1925. 

Professional experience: Assistant doctor at Sätra Spa in 1913, temporary assistant doctor at Västerås Hospital in 1915, second and first assistant doctor at Serafimer Hospital surgical clinic and outpatient clinic in 1917, first assistant doctor at Sundsvall Hospital surgical department from 1917 to 1923, including a ten-month period as temporary chief physician. Assistant doctor at the obstetrics-gynecology clinic in Uppsala from 1923 to 1924, assistant doctor at the surgical department of Maria Hospital from 1924 to 1926, temporary county physician in Skellefteå from 1926 to 1928, permanent county physician from 1928 to 1929, and practicing physician in Gothenburg since 1929. Doctor at Gothenburg City Hospital outpatient clinic in Majorna since 1933. Board member of Gothenburg City Free Clinic since 1940, temporary chief physician at Oscar and Maria Ekman Hospital from 1937 to 1938, surgeon at Renströmska Hospital since 1931, and preferred physician at Gothenburg City Recognized Central Health Insurance Fund from 1936 to 1946. Member of Gothenburg City Hospital Board of Directors from 1933 to 1936.

Publications: Works in the field of surgery.
